   <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>


    <h3>What is a "Satoshi" (sat)?</h3>
        <section>
            1 Satoshi = 0.00000001 Bitcoin. Conversely, 1 Bitcoin = 100,000,000 (100 Million) Satoshi.
        </section>

   <h3>I've been living under a rock the past year. What is Bitcoin (BTC)?</h3>
       <section>
           Bitcoin is a decentralized, digital currency. Visit <a href="http://bitcoin.org">bitcoin.org</a> or <a href="https://bitcointalk.org/">The Bitcoin Forum</a> to learn everything you want to know.
       </section>

