        <br>
        <i>*when withdrawing, normal <a href="https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/Transaction_fees">bitcoin transaction fees</a> (0.0001 BTC per transaction) still apply, these fees are collected by the Bitcoin network, not us</i>
        </section>

    <h3>My account says I have Bitcoins/Satoshi (real money).  But at tables, I have chips.  How does this work?</h3>
        <section>  
        <ul>
       <li> <i><b>When you buy in at a table:</i></b> your real money buy in amount is instantly converted to chips.  </li>
       
        <li><i><b>When u stand up from a table:</i></b> your chips at the table are instantly converted back to real money.</li>
       
        <li>We do this because displaying amounts in small decimals, or large numbers, such as: 0.00001, and 10000000 can be very easy to misread.</li>
       
        <li>At the top of each table, you will see a chip to currency ratio display that shows how much each chip is worth.</li>
        <ul>
        </section>

